     1→# Risk Governance and Gatekeeping
     2→
     3→## Principle
     4→
     5→Risk governance transforms subjective "should we ship?" debates into objective, data-driven decisions. By scoring risk (probability × impact), classifying by category (TECH, SEC, PERF, etc.), and tracking mitigation ownership, teams create transparent quality gates that balance speed with safety.
     6→
     7→## Rationale
     8→
     9→**The Problem**: Without formal risk governance, releases become political—loud voices win, quiet risks hide, and teams discover critical issues in production. "We thought it was fine" isn't a release strategy.
    10→
    11→**The Solution**: Risk scoring (1-3 scale for probability and impact, total 1-9) creates shared language. Scores ≥6 demand documented mitigation. Scores = 9 mandate gate failure. Every acceptance criterion maps to a test, and gaps require explicit waivers with owners and expiry dates.
    12→
    13→**Why This Matters**:
    14→
    15→- Removes ambiguity from release decisions (objective scores vs subjective opinions)
    16→- Creates audit trail for compliance (FDA, SOC2, ISO require documented risk management)
    17→- Identifies true blockers early (prevents last-minute production fires)
    18→- Distributes responsibility (owners, mitigation plans, deadlines for every risk >4)
    19→
    20→## Pattern Examples
    21→
    22→### Example 1: Risk Scoring Matrix with Automated Classification (TypeScript)
    23→
    24→**Context**: Calculate risk scores automatically from test results and categorize by risk type
    25→
    26→**Implementation**:
    27→
    28→```typescript
    29→// risk-scoring.ts - Risk classification and scoring system
    30→export const RISK_CATEGORIES = {
    31→  TECH: 'TECH', // Technical debt, architecture fragility
    32→  SEC: 'SEC', // Security vulnerabilities
    33→  PERF: 'PERF', // Performance degradation
    34→  DATA: 'DATA', // Data integrity, corruption
    35→  BUS: 'BUS', // Business logic errors
    36→  OPS: 'OPS', // Operational issues (deployment, monitoring)
    37→} as const;
    38→
    39→export type RiskCategory = keyof typeof RISK_CATEGORIES;
    40→
    41→export type RiskScore = {
    42→  id: string;
    43→  category: RiskCategory;
    44→  title: string;
    45→  description: string;
    46→  probability: 1 | 2 | 3; // 1=Low, 2=Medium, 3=High
    47→  impact: 1 | 2 | 3; // 1=Low, 2=Medium, 3=High
    48→  score: number; // probability × impact (1-9)
    49→  owner: string;
    50→  mitigationPlan?: string;
    51→  deadline?: Date;
    52→  status: 'OPEN' | 'MITIGATED' | 'WAIVED' | 'ACCEPTED';
    53→  waiverReason?: string;
    54→  waiverApprover?: string;
    55→  waiverExpiry?: Date;
    56→};
    57→
    58→// Risk scoring rules
    59→export function calculateRiskScore(probability: 1 | 2 | 3, impact: 1 | 2 | 3): number {
    60→  return probability * impact;
    61→}
    62→
    63→export function requiresMitigation(score: number): boolean {
    64→  return score >= 6; // Scores 6-9 demand action
    65→}
    66→
    67→export function isCriticalBlocker(score: number): boolean {
    68→  return score === 9; // Probability=3 AND Impact=3 → FAIL gate
    69→}
    70→
    71→export function classifyRiskLevel(score: number): 'LOW' | 'MEDIUM' | 'HIGH' | 'CRITICAL' {
    72→  if (score === 9) return 'CRITICAL';
    73→  if (score >= 6) return 'HIGH';
    74→  if (score >= 4) return 'MEDIUM';
    75→  return 'LOW';
    76→}
    77→
    78→// Example: Risk assessment from test failures
    79→export function assessTestFailureRisk(failure: {
    80→  test: string;
    81→  category: RiskCategory;
    82→  affectedUsers: number;
    83→  revenueImpact: number;
    84→  securityVulnerability: boolean;
    85→}): RiskScore {
    86→  // Probability based on test failure frequency (simplified)
    87→  const probability: 1 | 2 | 3 = 3; // Test failed = High probability
    88→
    89→  // Impact based on business context
    90→  let impact: 1 | 2 | 3 = 1;
    91→  if (failure.securityVulnerability) impact = 3;
    92→  else if (failure.revenueImpact > 10000) impact = 3;
    93→  else if (failure.affectedUsers > 1000) impact = 2;
    94→  else impact = 1;
    95→
    96→  const score = calculateRiskScore(probability, impact);
    97→
    98→  return {
    99→    id: `risk-${Date.now()}`,
   100→    category: failure.category,
   101→    title: `Test failure: ${failure.test}`,
   102→    description: `Affects ${failure.affectedUsers} users, $${failure.revenueImpact} revenue`,
   103→    probability,
   104→    impact,
   105→    score,
   106→    owner: 'unassigned',
   107→    status: score === 9 ? 'OPEN' : 'OPEN',
   108→  };
   109→}
   110→```
   111→
   112→**Key Points**:
   113→
   114→- **Objective scoring**: Probability (1-3) × Impact (1-3) = Score (1-9)
   115→- **Clear thresholds**: Score ≥6 requires mitigation, score = 9 blocks release
   116→- **Business context**: Revenue, users, security drive impact calculation
   117→- **Status tracking**: OPEN → MITIGATED → WAIVED → ACCEPTED lifecycle
   118→
   119→---
   120→
   121→### Example 2: Gate Decision Engine with Traceability Validation
   122→
   123→**Context**: Automated gate decision based on risk scores and test coverage
   124→
   125→**Implementation**:
   126→
   127→```typescript
   128→// gate-decision-engine.ts
   129→export type GateDecision = 'PASS' | 'CONCERNS' | 'FAIL' | 'WAIVED';
   130→
   131→export type CoverageGap = {
   132→  acceptanceCriteria: string;
   133→  testMissing: string;
   134→  reason: string;
   135→};
   136→
   137→export type GateResult = {
   138→  decision: GateDecision;
   139→  timestamp: Date;
   140→  criticalRisks: RiskScore[];
   141→  highRisks: RiskScore[];
   142→  coverageGaps: CoverageGap[];
   143→  summary: string;
   144→  recommendations: string[];
   145→};
   146→
   147→export function evaluateGate(params: { risks: RiskScore[]; coverageGaps: CoverageGap[]; waiverApprover?: string }): GateResult {
   148→  const { risks, coverageGaps, waiverApprover } = params;
   149→
   150→  // Categorize risks
   151→  const criticalRisks = risks.filter((r) => r.score === 9 && r.status === 'OPEN');
   152→  const highRisks = risks.filter((r) => r.score >= 6 && r.score < 9 && r.status === 'OPEN');
   153→  const unresolvedGaps = coverageGaps.filter((g) => !g.reason);
   154→
   155→  // Decision logic
   156→  let decision: GateDecision;
   157→
   158→  // FAIL: Critical blockers (score=9) or missing coverage
   159→  if (criticalRisks.length > 0 || unresolvedGaps.length > 0) {
   160→    decision = 'FAIL';
   161→  }
   162→  // WAIVED: All risks waived by authorized approver
   163→  else if (risks.every((r) => r.status === 'WAIVED') && waiverApprover) {
   164→    decision = 'WAIVED';
   165→  }
   166→  // CONCERNS: High risks (score 6-8) with mitigation plans
   167→  else if (highRisks.length > 0 && highRisks.every((r) => r.mitigationPlan && r.owner !== 'unassigned')) {
   168→    decision = 'CONCERNS';
   169→  }
   170→  // PASS: No critical issues, all risks mitigated or low
   171→  else {
   172→    decision = 'PASS';
   173→  }
   174→
   175→  // Generate recommendations
   176→  const recommendations: string[] = [];
   177→  if (criticalRisks.length > 0) {
   178→    recommendations.push(`🚨 ${criticalRisks.length} CRITICAL risk(s) must be mitigated before release`);
   179→  }
   180→  if (unresolvedGaps.length > 0) {
   181→    recommendations.push(`📋 ${unresolvedGaps.length} acceptance criteria lack test coverage`);
   182→  }
   183→  if (highRisks.some((r) => !r.mitigationPlan)) {
   184→    recommendations.push(`⚠️  High risks without mitigation plans: assign owners and deadlines`);
   185→  }
   186→  if (decision === 'PASS') {
   187→    recommendations.push(`✅ All risks mitigated or acceptable. Ready for release.`);
   188→  }
   189→
   190→  return {
   191→    decision,
   192→    timestamp: new Date(),
   193→    criticalRisks,
   194→    highRisks,
   195→    coverageGaps: unresolvedGaps,
   196→    summary: generateSummary(decision, risks, unresolvedGaps),
   197→    recommendations,
   198→  };
   199→}
   200→
   201→function generateSummary(decision: GateDecision, risks: RiskScore[], gaps: CoverageGap[]): string {
   202→  const total = risks.length;
   203→  const critical = risks.filter((r) => r.score === 9).length;
   204→  const high = risks.filter((r) => r.score >= 6 && r.score < 9).length;
   205→
   206→  return `Gate Decision: ${decision}. Total Risks: ${total} (${critical} critical, ${high} high). Coverage Gaps: ${gaps.length}.`;
   207→}
   208→```
   209→
   210→**Usage Example**:
   211→
   212→```typescript
   213→// Example: Running gate check before deployment
   214→import { assessTestFailureRisk, evaluateGate } from './gate-decision-engine';
   215→
   216→// Collect risks from test results
   217→const risks: RiskScore[] = [
   218→  assessTestFailureRisk({
   219→    test: 'Payment processing with expired card',
   220→    category: 'BUS',
   221→    affectedUsers: 5000,
   222→    revenueImpact: 50000,
   223→    securityVulnerability: false,
   224→  }),
   225→  assessTestFailureRisk({
   226→    test: 'SQL injection in search endpoint',
   227→    category: 'SEC',
   228→    affectedUsers: 10000,
   229→    revenueImpact: 0,
   230→    securityVulnerability: true,
   231→  }),
   232→];
   233→
   234→// Identify coverage gaps
   235→const coverageGaps: CoverageGap[] = [
   236→  {
   237→    acceptanceCriteria: 'User can reset password via email',
   238→    testMissing: 'e2e/auth/password-reset.spec.ts',
   239→    reason: '', // Empty = unresolved
   240→  },
   241→];
   242→
   243→// Evaluate gate
   244→const gateResult = evaluateGate({ risks, coverageGaps });
   245→
   246→console.log(gateResult.decision); // 'FAIL'
   247→console.log(gateResult.summary);
   248→// "Gate Decision: FAIL. Total Risks: 2 (1 critical, 1 high). Coverage Gaps: 1."
   249→
   250→console.log(gateResult.recommendations);
   251→// [
   252→//   "🚨 1 CRITICAL risk(s) must be mitigated before release",
   253→//   "📋 1 acceptance criteria lack test coverage"
   254→// ]
   255→```
   256→
   257→**Key Points**:
   258→
   259→- **Automated decision**: No human interpretation required
   260→- **Clear criteria**: FAIL = critical risks or gaps, CONCERNS = high risks with plans, PASS = low risks
   261→- **Actionable output**: Recommendations drive next steps
   262→- **Audit trail**: Timestamp, decision, and context for compliance
   263→
   264→---
   265→
   266→### Example 3: Risk Mitigation Workflow with Owner Tracking
   267→
   268→**Context**: Track risk mitigation from identification to resolution
   269→
   270→**Implementation**:
   271→
   272→```typescript
   273→// risk-mitigation.ts
   274→export type MitigationAction = {
   275→  riskId: string;
   276→  action: string;
   277→  owner: string;
   278→  deadline: Date;
   279→  status: 'PENDING' | 'IN_PROGRESS' | 'COMPLETED' | 'BLOCKED';
   280→  completedAt?: Date;
   281→  blockedReason?: string;
   282→};
   283→
   284→export class RiskMitigationTracker {
   285→  private risks: Map<string, RiskScore> = new Map();
   286→  private actions: Map<string, MitigationAction[]> = new Map();
   287→  private history: Array<{ riskId: string; event: string; timestamp: Date }> = [];
   288→
   289→  // Register a new risk
   290→  addRisk(risk: RiskScore): void {
   291→    this.risks.set(risk.id, risk);
   292→    this.logHistory(risk.id, `Risk registered: ${risk.title} (Score: ${risk.score})`);
   293→
   294→    // Auto-assign mitigation requirements for score ≥6
   295→    if (requiresMitigation(risk.score) && !risk.mitigationPlan) {
   296→      this.logHistory(risk.id, `⚠️  Mitigation required (score ${risk.score}). Assign owner and plan.`);
   297→    }
   298→  }
   299→
   300→  // Add mitigation action
   301→  addMitigationAction(action: MitigationAction): void {
   302→    const risk = this.risks.get(action.riskId);
   303→    if (!risk) throw new Error(`Risk ${action.riskId} not found`);
   304→
   305→    const existingActions = this.actions.get(action.riskId) || [];
   306→    existingActions.push(action);
   307→    this.actions.set(action.riskId, existingActions);
   308→
   309→    this.logHistory(action.riskId, `Mitigation action added: ${action.action} (Owner: ${action.owner})`);
   310→  }
   311→
   312→  // Complete mitigation action
   313→  completeMitigation(riskId: string, actionIndex: number): void {
   314→    const actions = this.actions.get(riskId);
   315→    if (!actions || !actions[actionIndex]) throw new Error('Action not found');
   316→
   317→    actions[actionIndex].status = 'COMPLETED';
   318→    actions[actionIndex].completedAt = new Date();
   319→
   320→    this.logHistory(riskId, `Mitigation completed: ${actions[actionIndex].action}`);
   321→
   322→    // If all actions completed, mark risk as MITIGATED
   323→    if (actions.every((a) => a.status === 'COMPLETED')) {
   324→      const risk = this.risks.get(riskId)!;
   325→      risk.status = 'MITIGATED';
   326→      this.logHistory(riskId, `✅ Risk mitigated. All actions complete.`);
   327→    }
   328→  }
   329→
   330→  // Request waiver for a risk
   331→  requestWaiver(riskId: string, reason: string, approver: string, expiryDays: number): void {
   332→    const risk = this.risks.get(riskId);
   333→    if (!risk) throw new Error(`Risk ${riskId} not found`);
   334→
   335→    risk.status = 'WAIVED';
   336→    risk.waiverReason = reason;
   337→    risk.waiverApprover = approver;
   338→    risk.waiverExpiry = new Date(Date.now() + expiryDays * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
   339→
   340→    this.logHistory(riskId, `⚠️  Waiver granted by ${approver}. Expires: ${risk.waiverExpiry}`);
   341→  }
   342→
   343→  // Generate risk report
   344→  generateReport(): string {
   345→    const allRisks = Array.from(this.risks.values());
   346→    const critical = allRisks.filter((r) => r.score === 9 && r.status === 'OPEN');
   347→    const high = allRisks.filter((r) => r.score >= 6 && r.score < 9 && r.status === 'OPEN');
   348→    const mitigated = allRisks.filter((r) => r.status === 'MITIGATED');
   349→    const waived = allRisks.filter((r) => r.status === 'WAIVED');
   350→
   351→    let report = `# Risk Mitigation Report\n\n`;
   352→    report += `**Generated**: ${new Date().toISOString()}\n\n`;
   353→    report += `## Summary\n`;
   354→    report += `- Total Risks: ${allRisks.length}\n`;
   355→    report += `- Critical (Score=9, OPEN): ${critical.length}\n`;
   356→    report += `- High (Score 6-8, OPEN): ${high.length}\n`;
   357→    report += `- Mitigated: ${mitigated.length}\n`;
   358→    report += `- Waived: ${waived.length}\n\n`;
   359→
   360→    if (critical.length > 0) {
   361→      report += `## 🚨 Critical Risks (BLOCKERS)\n\n`;
   362→      critical.forEach((r) => {
   363→        report += `- **${r.title}** (${r.category})\n`;
   364→        report += `  - Score: ${r.score} (Probability: ${r.probability}, Impact: ${r.impact})\n`;
   365→        report += `  - Owner: ${r.owner}\n`;
   366→        report += `  - Mitigation: ${r.mitigationPlan || 'NOT ASSIGNED'}\n\n`;
   367→      });
   368→    }
   369→
   370→    if (high.length > 0) {
   371→      report += `## ⚠️  High Risks\n\n`;
   372→      high.forEach((r) => {
   373→        report += `- **${r.title}** (${r.category})\n`;
   374→        report += `  - Score: ${r.score}\n`;
   375→        report += `  - Owner: ${r.owner}\n`;
   376→        report += `  - Deadline: ${r.deadline?.toISOString().split('T')[0] || 'NOT SET'}\n\n`;
   377→      });
   378→    }
   379→
   380→    return report;
   381→  }
   382→
   383→  private logHistory(riskId: string, event: string): void {
   384→    this.history.push({ riskId, event, timestamp: new Date() });
   385→  }
   386→
   387→  getHistory(riskId: string): Array<{ event: string; timestamp: Date }> {
   388→    return this.history.filter((h) => h.riskId === riskId).map((h) => ({ event: h.event, timestamp: h.timestamp }));
   389→  }
   390→}
   391→```
   392→
   393→**Usage Example**:
   394→
   395→```typescript
   396→const tracker = new RiskMitigationTracker();
   397→
   398→// Register critical security risk
   399→tracker.addRisk({
   400→  id: 'risk-001',
   401→  category: 'SEC',
   402→  title: 'SQL injection vulnerability in user search',
   403→  description: 'Unsanitized input allows arbitrary SQL execution',
   404→  probability: 3,
   405→  impact: 3,
   406→  score: 9,
   407→  owner: 'security-team',
   408→  status: 'OPEN',
   409→});
   410→
   411→// Add mitigation actions
   412→tracker.addMitigationAction({
   413→  riskId: 'risk-001',
   414→  action: 'Add parameterized queries to user-search endpoint',
   415→  owner: 'alice@example.com',
   416→  deadline: new Date('2025-10-20'),
   417→  status: 'IN_PROGRESS',
   418→});
   419→
   420→tracker.addMitigationAction({
   421→  riskId: 'risk-001',
   422→  action: 'Add WAF rule to block SQL injection patterns',
   423→  owner: 'bob@example.com',
   424→  deadline: new Date('2025-10-22'),
   425→  status: 'PENDING',
   426→});
   427→
   428→// Complete first action
   429→tracker.completeMitigation('risk-001', 0);
   430→
   431→// Generate report
   432→console.log(tracker.generateReport());
   433→// Markdown report with critical risks, owners, deadlines
   434→
   435→// View history
   436→console.log(tracker.getHistory('risk-001'));
   437→// [
   438→//   { event: 'Risk registered: SQL injection...', timestamp: ... },
   439→//   { event: 'Mitigation action added: Add parameterized queries...', timestamp: ... },
   440→//   { event: 'Mitigation completed: Add parameterized queries...', timestamp: ... }
   441→// ]
   442→```
   443→
   444→**Key Points**:
   445→
   446→- **Ownership enforcement**: Every risk >4 requires owner assignment
   447→- **Deadline tracking**: Mitigation actions have explicit deadlines
   448→- **Audit trail**: Complete history of risk lifecycle (registered → mitigated)
   449→- **Automated reports**: Markdown output for Confluence/GitHub wikis
   450→
   451→---
   452→
   453→### Example 4: Coverage Traceability Matrix (Test-to-Requirement Mapping)
   454→
   455→**Context**: Validate that every acceptance criterion maps to at least one test
   456→
   457→**Implementation**:
   458→
   459→```typescript
   460→// coverage-traceability.ts
   461→export type AcceptanceCriterion = {
   462→  id: string;
   463→  story: string;
   464→  criterion: string;
   465→  priority: 'P0' | 'P1' | 'P2' | 'P3';
   466→};
   467→
   468→export type TestCase = {
   469→  file: string;
   470→  name: string;
   471→  criteriaIds: string[]; // Links to acceptance criteria
   472→};
   473→
   474→export type CoverageMatrix = {
   475→  criterion: AcceptanceCriterion;
   476→  tests: TestCase[];
   477→  covered: boolean;
   478→  waiverReason?: string;
   479→};
   480→
   481→export function buildCoverageMatrix(criteria: AcceptanceCriterion[], tests: TestCase[]): CoverageMatrix[] {
   482→  return criteria.map((criterion) => {
   483→    const matchingTests = tests.filter((t) => t.criteriaIds.includes(criterion.id));
   484→
   485→    return {
   486→      criterion,
   487→      tests: matchingTests,
   488→      covered: matchingTests.length > 0,
   489→    };
   490→  });
   491→}
   492→
   493→export function validateCoverage(matrix: CoverageMatrix[]): {
   494→  gaps: CoverageMatrix[];
   495→  passRate: number;
   496→} {
   497→  const gaps = matrix.filter((m) => !m.covered && !m.waiverReason);
   498→  const passRate = ((matrix.length - gaps.length) / matrix.length) * 100;
   499→
   500→  return { gaps, passRate };
   501→}
   502→
   503→// Example: Extract criteria IDs from test names
   504→export function extractCriteriaFromTests(testFiles: string[]): TestCase[] {
   505→  // Simplified: In real implementation, parse test files with AST
   506→  // Here we simulate extraction from test names
   507→  return [
   508→    {
   509→      file: 'tests/e2e/auth/login.spec.ts',
   510→      name: 'should allow user to login with valid credentials',
   511→      criteriaIds: ['AC-001', 'AC-002'], // Linked to acceptance criteria
   512→    },
   513→    {
   514→      file: 'tests/e2e/auth/password-reset.spec.ts',
   515→      name: 'should send password reset email',
   516→      criteriaIds: ['AC-003'],
   517→    },
   518→  ];
   519→}
   520→
   521→// Generate Markdown traceability report
   522→export function generateTraceabilityReport(matrix: CoverageMatrix[]): string {
   523→  let report = `# Requirements-to-Tests Traceability Matrix\n\n`;
   524→  report += `**Generated**: ${new Date().toISOString()}\n\n`;
   525→
   526→  const { gaps, passRate } = validateCoverage(matrix);
   527→
   528→  report += `## Summary\n`;
   529→  report += `- Total Criteria: ${matrix.length}\n`;
   530→  report += `- Covered: ${matrix.filter((m) => m.covered).length}\n`;
   531→  report += `- Gaps: ${gaps.length}\n`;
   532→  report += `- Waived: ${matrix.filter((m) => m.waiverReason).length}\n`;
   533→  report += `- Coverage Rate: ${passRate.toFixed(1)}%\n\n`;
   534→
   535→  if (gaps.length > 0) {
   536→    report += `## ❌ Coverage Gaps (MUST RESOLVE)\n\n`;
   537→    report += `| Story | Criterion | Priority | Tests |\n`;
   538→    report += `|-------|-----------|----------|-------|\n`;
   539→    gaps.forEach((m) => {
   540→      report += `| ${m.criterion.story} | ${m.criterion.criterion} | ${m.criterion.priority} | None |\n`;
   541→    });
   542→    report += `\n`;
   543→  }
   544→
   545→  report += `## ✅ Covered Criteria\n\n`;
   546→  report += `| Story | Criterion | Tests |\n`;
   547→  report += `|-------|-----------|-------|\n`;
   548→  matrix
   549→    .filter((m) => m.covered)
   550→    .forEach((m) => {
   551→      const testList = m.tests.map((t) => `\`${t.file}\``).join(', ');
   552→      report += `| ${m.criterion.story} | ${m.criterion.criterion} | ${testList} |\n`;
   553→    });
   554→
   555→  return report;
   556→}
   557→```
   558→
   559→**Usage Example**:
   560→
   561→```typescript
   562→// Define acceptance criteria
   563→const criteria: AcceptanceCriterion[] = [
   564→  { id: 'AC-001', story: 'US-123', criterion: 'User can login with email', priority: 'P0' },
   565→  { id: 'AC-002', story: 'US-123', criterion: 'User sees error on invalid password', priority: 'P0' },
   566→  { id: 'AC-003', story: 'US-124', criterion: 'User receives password reset email', priority: 'P1' },
   567→  { id: 'AC-004', story: 'US-125', criterion: 'User can update profile', priority: 'P2' }, // NO TEST
   568→];
   569→
   570→// Extract tests
